- The integer array parameter `weights` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `weights` must contain weights of packages to be shipped.
- The integer parameter `days` represents the number of days within which all packages must be shipped.
- The integer result is the least weight capacity of the ship that will result in all the packages on the conveyor belt being shipped within `days` days.
- The order of packages on the conveyor belt must be maintained while loading the ship.
- The ship cannot load more weight than its maximum weight capacity.
- The ship must ship all the packages within the specified number of days.
- The ship must follow the order of packages given by `weights` while shipping.
- The ship must ship the packages in the order given by `weights` without splitting them into parts.
- The ship must ship the packages in the order given by `weights` without rearranging them.